  "prompt": "What are the pros and cons of booking flights through a travel site compared to direct bookings with the airline?",
  "response": "Here's a breakdown of pros and cons:\n\nTravel Site Pros:\n- Can compare prices across multiple airlines\n- Often offer package deals with hotels/car rentals\n- Sometimes have exclusive discounts\n- Convenient one-stop booking\n- May offer price matching\n- Some sites have price prediction tools\n\nTravel Site Cons:\n- Additional booking fees\n- Less direct customer service\n- More complicated to make changes/cancellations\n- Might have less flexibility with seat selection\n- Potential communication delays\n- Risk of third-party booking complications\n\nAirline Direct Booking Pros:\n- Direct customer service\n- Easier flight changes/cancellations\n- Typically more seat selection options\n- Earn airline loyalty points directly\n- Clearer communication\n- Sometimes lower base prices\n- More control over booking\n\nAirline Direct Booking Cons:\n- Need to check multiple airline sites\n- Might miss comparative pricing\n- Fewer bundled deal options\n- Can be more time-consuming\n- Limited to single airline's offerings\n\nThe best option depends on individual travel needs, preferences, and specific trip details.",
